Messages.Value: Thank you for calling the travel agency, this is Ethan James. How may I assist you today?
Yes, hi. I'm calling because I'm having trouble with the app on my phone. I can't seem to log in and I have travel plans coming up next week.
I apologize for the inconvenience. Can you please confirm your name and destination city so I can pull up your information?
My name is Sarah Smith and I'm traveling to New York City.
Thank you, Sarah. I have pulled up your reservation and I can see that you have a flight with United Airlines from Los Angeles to New York City on June 20th at 6:00pm. Is this correct?
Thank you. Can you please tell me more about the issue you are experiencing with the app?
I'm trying to log in with my email and password, but it keeps telling me that my password is incorrect. I've tried resetting it multiple times, but it still won't work.
I'm sorry to hear that, Sarah. Let me see if I can assist you with this. Can you please confirm the email address associated with your account?
Thank you. One moment please while I check on this.

I'm sorry, Sarah, but it seems like your account has been locked due to too many failed login attempts. I'm going to need to log a ticket and have our technical support team reach out to you to assist with unlocking your account. Is there a phone number or email address where they can reach you?
Yes, my phone number is 555-123-4567 and my email is sarah.smith@gmail.com.
Thank you, Sarah. I will log a ticket and our technical support team will reach out to you to assist with unlocking your account.
I apologize for any inconvenience this has caused, Sarah. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?
No, that's all. Thanks for your help.
